From: Bogdan Hamciuc <bogdan.hamciuc@nxp.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jan 2020 11:04:04 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 057/269] s32g: Do not init SRAM area for BL31 any longer

BL31 is now in DDR.

Upstream-Status: Pending 

Signed-off-by: Bogdan Hamciuc <bogdan.hamciuc@nxp.com>
Signed-off-by: Zhantao Tang <zhantao.tang@windriver.com>
Issue: ALB-4474
---
 plat/s32g/s32g_lowlevel_bl2.S | 5 -----
 1 file changed, 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/plat/s32g/s32g_lowlevel_bl2.S b/plat/s32g/s32g_lowlevel_bl2.S
index ba8726ed1..be8efe07e 100644
--- a/plat/s32g/s32g_lowlevel_bl2.S
+++ b/plat/s32g/s32g_lowlevel_bl2.S
@@ -47,11 +47,6 @@ func plat_reset_handler
 	ldr	x1,=__BL2_END__
 	sub	x1, x1, x0
 	bl	s32g_sram_init
-	/* Target area for BL31 needs to be initialized, also */
-	ldr	x0,=BL31_BASE
-	ldr	x1,=BL31_LIMIT
-	sub	x1, x1, x0
-	bl	s32g_sram_init
 
 	mov	x30, x7
 	ret
